## Gotchas
- func.attributes is read directly in _create_call (not getattr); every op created
  via op() sets wrapper.attributes (None default), and deserialized ops are
  reconstructed via @weave.op, so the attribute always exists.
- importlib.metadata.version returns PEP440-normalized strings (0.52.43.dev0) which
  can differ in punctuation from weave.version.VERSION (0.52.43-dev0); tests account
  for this.

